Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Bimodal test problem", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9334043059496875`*^9, 3.9334043136954947`*^9}, {
  3.9334043730189486`*^9, 3.9334043759706955`*^9}},
 FontSize->24,ExpressionUUID->"2a8a418b-c6bd-429c-8ddb-e612852d9539"],

Cell["\<\
This code test prediction quality of the Gramian and extended Gramian \
closures for the (n + 1)^th
moment given the set of n lower moments. We consider a strongly bimodal \
distribution which is designed
using a superposition of two Gaussian with different velocities. We compare \
the moment prediction with Grad\[CloseCurlyQuote]s closure and maximum \
entropy closure.  Details about Gramian and extended Gramian closures with \
different test problems can be found in the following paper  \
https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.05894\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9334043797824507`*^9, 3.933404388342066*^9}, {
  3.9339065760670166`*^9, 3.9339065778042517`*^9}, {3.933907321765495*^9, 
  3.9339073439639626`*^9}, {3.933907589544405*^9, 3.933907685063188*^9}, {
  3.933907738235751*^9, 3.9339078044023657`*^9}, {3.9339078598785706`*^9, 
  3.9339079506807203`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a7b390fd-3748-4a1a-9269-\
531b6fa05fa8"],

